# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Create Azure Service Principal:
#    az ad sp create-for-rbac --name "AgentCarRepair" --role "Cognitive Services Contributor"
#
# 2. Get your Azure AI Foundry project endpoint:
#    - Go to Azure portal > Your AI Foundry project
#    - Copy the endpoint URL from the overview page
#
# 3. Find your agent ID:
#    - Go to your AI Foundry project
#    - Navigate to Agents section
#    - Copy the ID of your car repair agent
#
# 4. Generate a secure Flask secret key:
#    python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
#
# 5. Set appropriate permissions:
#    - Your service principal needs "Cognitive Services Contributor" role
#    - Ensure it has access to your AI Foundry project
#
# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# - Keep your .env file private and never commit it to version control
# - Use strong, unique values for AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET and FLASK_SECRET_KEY
# - Rotate credentials regularly for production environments
# - Consider using Azure Key Vault for production deployments
# - Set FLASK_DEBUG=False in production environments
#
